# Live TV & EPG Guide UI

Architecture: SwiftData store → `EPGBrowseLoader` → `LiveTVSectionEPGCache` → list + guide. See `EPG.md` and Build 19 in `PROJECT_REFERENCE.md`.

## Required patterns

```swift
// ✅ List + guide both mounted; shared cache
ZStack {
  ChannelsList(..., sectionToken: section.id, epgCache: epgCache)
    .opacity(layoutMode == .list ? 1 : 0)
  EPGGuideView(..., sectionToken: section.id, epgCache: epgCache)
    .opacity(layoutMode == .guide ? 1 : 0)
}
.id(contentSort.rawValue)  // sort only — NOT section or layout

// ✅ Same loader as list — no guide-only window
await EPGBrowseLoader.load(container:channels:playlist:)

// ✅ Merge missing channels only
epgCache.merge(section: sectionToken, loaded: loaded)

// ✅ Category switch — reset pagination only
.onChange(of: sectionToken) { visibleCount = LiveChannelQuery.pageSize }
```

## Forbidden

- `.id("\(section)-\(sort)-\(layout)")` or any `.id()` keyed on category
- `if layoutMode == .guide { EPGGuideView } else { ChannelsList }` (destroys state)
- `programsByChannel = [:]` / `epgByChannel = [:]` on `sectionToken` change
- `playlist(for:)` fetch when `activePlaylist` is available — pass `playlist:` prop
- `windowStart`/`windowEnd` on guide's `EPGBrowseLoader.load` (narrows store vs list)
- `replace: true` that replaces entire cache dict instead of merge
